defaultFemale fans experience lifelong attachments to their clubs which are rather more complex than previous studies have indicated; the stereotypes that all 
defaultwomen go to football just as adjuncts to male partners or to display 'femaleness' by gazing at male sportsmen are not necessarily empirically true (although none of my respondents practised their fandom in such a way, it is possible that such fans may exis
defaultt).
